{"title": "Narrative of Sojourner Truth", "description": "The Narrative of Sojourner Truth is the gripping autobiographical account of Sojourner Truths life as a slave in pre-Civil War New York State, and her eventual escape to Freedom. Since Sojourner could neither read or write, she dictated her story to Olive Gilbert after they met at a Women\u2019s Rights rally. The Narrative was first published in 1850, and was widely distributed by the Abolitionist Movement. It was one of the catalysts for the rise of anti-slavery public opinion in the years leading up to the Civil War. Though Olive Gilbert's writing about Sojourner takes on a patronizing tone at times (a weakness of some Abolitionists), The Narrative of Sojourner Truth remains a moving and historic document, chronicling the struggles of African-Americans under slavery and the life of a truly remarkable woman. (Introduction by Marc Kockinos)", "duration": 15814, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2900", "name": "Olive Gilbert"}, {"id": "5706", "name": " Sojourner Truth"}], "coverArt": "http://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt21/narrative_sojourner_truth_1208.jpg", "copyright_year": "1850", "genres": ["*Non-fiction", "Biography & Autobiography", "History"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Annise"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "01 - HER BIRTH AND PARENTAGE", "readers": [5991], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/narrative_sojourner_truth_1204_librivox/narrativeofsojournertruth_01_gilbert_truth_64kb.mp3", "duration": 132}, {"section": 2, "title": "02 - ACCOMMODATIONS", "readers": [5991], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/narrative_sojourner_truth_1204_librivox/narrativeofsojournertruth_02_gilbert_truth_64kb.mp3", "duration": 173}, {"section": 3, "title": "03 - HER BROTHERS AND SISTERS", "readers": [5991], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/narrativ